# Motia Streams

Streams push live updates from backend to connected clients without polling. Define streams in `*.stream.ts` files.

## Defining a Stream

```typescript
// src/my-entity.stream.ts
import { StreamConfig } from 'motia'
import { z } from 'zod'

export const config: StreamConfig = {
  name: 'myEntity',
  schema: z.object({
    id: z.string(),
    status: z.string(),
    updatedAt: z.string(),
  }),
  baseConfig: { storageType: 'default' },
}
```

Motia auto-discovers the stream and exposes it as `ctx.streams.myEntity` in all step handlers.

## Stream Methods (in step handlers)

```typescript
await ctx.streams.myEntity.set(groupId, id, data)       // Create/update (pushes to clients)
await ctx.streams.myEntity.get(groupId, id)              // Get single item
await ctx.streams.myEntity.delete(groupId, id)           // Remove item
await ctx.streams.myEntity.getGroup(groupId)             // Get all items in group
await ctx.streams.myEntity.update(groupId, id, ops)      // Atomic update with UpdateOp[]
await ctx.streams.myEntity.send(channel, event)          // Ephemeral event (no persistence)
```

Every `set()` call automatically pushes updates to all subscribed clients.

## Ephemeral Events

For transient data like typing indicators that shouldn't be persisted:

```typescript
await ctx.streams.chat.send(
  { groupId: channelId },
  { type: 'typing', data: { userId: 'user-123', isTyping: true } }
)
```

## Access Control

```typescript
export const config: StreamConfig = {
  name: 'myEntity',
  schema: mySchema,
  baseConfig: { storageType: 'default' },
  canAccess: ({ groupId, id }, authContext) => {
    return authContext?.projectIds.includes(groupId) ?? false
  },
  onJoin: async (subscription, context, authContext) => {
    if (!authContext?.userId) return { unauthorized: true }
    return { unauthorized: false }
  },
  onLeave: async (subscription, context, authContext) => {
    context.logger.info('Client left', { subscription })
  },
}
```

## Stream Triggers in Steps

Steps can react to stream changes:

```typescript
triggers: [{
  type: 'stream',
  streamName: 'myEntity',
  groupId: 'data',
  condition: (input) => input.event.type === 'update',
}]
```

## Frontend React Integration

```typescript
import { MotiaStreamProvider, useStreamGroup } from 'motia/stream-client-react'

// Wrap app
<MotiaStreamProvider address="ws://localhost:3000" authToken={token}>
  <App />
</MotiaStreamProvider>

// Subscribe to a group
const { data } = useStreamGroup<MyEntity>({ groupId: 'inbox', streamName: 'myEntity' })
```
